# Aerial Playground -- the lead, stripped back: one exposed triangle
# core, no stacked unison to hide behind -- just the ladder's own
# drift and mismatch left audible. Osc 2 sits a tritone up but at
# ZERO level in the plain mix; it exists only to feed the ring
# modulator, so every note gets a faint inharmonic shimmer at its own
# tritone -- the same interval the melody leaps by -- instead of a
# chromatic "wrong" note. Long glide and release: it swells in and
# slides between the wide leaps rather than snapping to pitch.
waveform 3
osc2_wave 0
osc2_pitch 6
osc2_level 0
osc3_wave 0
osc3_pitch 0
osc3_level 0
detune 3
sub 0
circuit 0
key_track 0.5
osc_fm 0
sync 0
ring 0.16
glide 0.09
pulse_width 0.5
attack 0.05
decay 0.5
sustain 0.68
release 1.1
filter_env 0.4
filter_attack 0.05
filter_decay 0.5
filter_sustain 0.6
filter_release 1.0
cutoff 1500
resonance 0.7
drive 1.3
saturation 1.0
hpf 50
